text: C. M. and Vina Clark House, also known as Rosemont and Clark Welling House, is a historic home located at Montrose, Henry County, Missouri. It was built in 1913, and is 1 1/2-story brick and frame dwelling with a combination of Late Victorian and Colonial Revival style design elements. (includes 35 photographs from 1995-1996) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1997. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Victorian architecture in Missouri Category:Colonial Revival architecture in Missouri Category:Houses completed in 1913 Category:Buildings and structures in Henry County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Henry County, Missouri
